verses.roman:
ei-mate sevaka-prabhu duṅhe ghara gelā
āra dina jagadānanda sanātanere mililā

synonyms: ei-mate—in this way; sevaka-prabhu—the servant and the master; duṅhe—both of them; ghara gelā—returned to their respective places; āra dina—the next day; jagadānanda—Jagadānanda; sanātanere mililā—met Sanātana Gosvāmī.
translation: Thus both servant and master departed for their respective homes. The next day, Jagadānanda Paṇḍita went to meet Sanātana Gosvāmī.
